text: Well, I will avoid this like the plague if I can. The trailer makes this film look just as bad as God's Not Dead. I'm fine with people having religious beliefs, that's their choice, but God's Not Dead was poorly made. Awful acting, the teacher gave an okay performance though, but the writing was so bad it hurt. I get that you want to make your movie have a message, but it's so misinformed and preachy that I found it unwatchable. The concept alone is ridiculous; it's clear that the people on campus know how the teacher is, yet he's still working. In reality, he'd be fired in a heartbeat. But to me, the biggest insult is how they portray anyone who isn't Christian. Every Atheist in the movie is played as a despicable human being with no redeeming qualities whatsoever. The line stating that every Atheist was once religious is also false. Think of Atheist parents raising a child, they're not going to raise them religiously, so they never were religious in the first place. Like I said, I'm not hating on religion. If you believe in God, good for you, I have no problem with it, nor should I. If you like this movie, while I wholeheartedly disagree on its quality, I will at least respect your opinion, I just want to be able to express mine in return. I doubt this will be much better, so I doubt I'll ever watch it. Cheers!

text: It's unfortunate that Atheists make such an effort to seek out hypocritical, flakey so called "Christians" rather than the ones out there trying to emulate what they believe and to impart to others the truth of God's grace, not "Judgement". The heart of a true Christian is to simply care, serve and impart to others.. I won't lump all atheists together simply because many of the ones I see on blogs are hate mongering on Christians for their lack of tolerance, while missing the glaring contradictions in every aspect of their approach. I'm sure there are many intelligent Atheists out there that can impart their reasoning in a thoughtful and respectful way to other people, including Christians, without offending. Faith is a confusing issue for many people. And of course, many people have negative experiences within the church. It's human nature to foster the need for black and white constructs to protect ourselves from more hurt... which is why divorce rates only get higher after the failure of a first marriage. Rather than learning from the experience, people develop a more rigid approach to marriage and they become confined by those constructs. The truth is, you can't avoid getting hurt, all you can do is try to learn and grow from it. ¬†You can't run from the fact that their is suffering in the world, all you can do is try to lend a hand. You can't run from the fact that heartbreak comes to your door whether your looking for it or not. None of these things are simple to understand or define. I believe in God, but I can't prove He exists to a person that doesn't want to see Him in the gifts that life brings or want to see an "angry" God who hates homosexuals and so on.. I don't see God that way.I see God as merciful and gracious.. A God that states that "His mercy endures forever.. and His mercies are new every morning".. I believe the truth of the bible requires context, discernment and a desire to find truth to truly grasp the message and intent. Whether you believe in God or not.. Life is a mystery to us all. What I would want to make sure of is that I did everything I could to unravel the mystery of life, rather than simply dismissing the notion of God to justify such a short term existence. If Atheists are right.. there will be no way to ever gloat about it.. Unfortunately, if they are wrong... I believe God will ask one question of everyone.. Did you invest your whole heart in trying to find me before you gave up? If there is a God, surely He is worth seeking.¬†

text: For those of you who are looking for 100% proof for the same God that we followers of Jesus Christ believe in, stop wasting your time searching for evidence beyond any shadow of doubt--you won't find it. Even if the God of the Bible were to step down and meet with you, for but a few minutes, you'd still find a way to discount His appearance to you at that moment. We could go round and round and round all day long--and on into the night--and you'd find a way to ignore everything I'm sharing with you for Who God is and why folks like me believe He exists just as described in the Bible. So, I leave you with this challenge: Call out to Him--as silly as this may initially seem to you--and ask Him to show Himself to you. His Word tell us that if you do seek after Him--with all your heart--He WILL show Himself to you. If He does not exist, you have nothing to lose; if He DOES exist, you have everything to gain, namely your soul and eternal companionship with Him. Just saying.

text: Once we believed the earth was flat (it's not); once we believed the earth was round¬†(it's not); once we believe the¬†sun revolved around the earth, once we¬†didn't believe in electricity, once we believed that DNA was impossible to replicate and free innocent prisoners. Once we believed that a primordial soup brought about life (now a change to some type of¬†primitive protein¬†-amino acids), If you look at it, only two species are required to manage life on earth -predator and prey (never thought of until recently), once we believed that the universe was eventually become an singularity -now we see it's expanding. Once we believed in only the cells, not the mitochondria. Once we¬†believed doctors could only pronounce a disease not save. Sean Astin's disbelief doesn't mean God doesn't work through non-believers.¬†Once we that there was no Big Bang. Now, it's theorized. To make a theory of evolution on one man's observations is like walking across a clearly falling bridge.¬†Even Einstein believed in one unifying theory but was unable to verify it, and left it to God. Each subsequent rocket scientist has¬†worked on theories that end up in¬†one answer,¬†and considered impossible: eternity. Since evolution and the workings of the universe are ¬†THEORIES, and cannot be adequately reproduced,¬†¬†how can you place your eggs in that basket? Yet, time and again, bees produce bees, trees produce trees - reproducible throughout the ages, and people are gifted with special gifts - the scientist, the doctors, the nurses, the speakers, the preachers. Why? Because through everyone - God bestows gifts to give hope and life and the resurrection of Christ. Whether or not one believes, God loves everyone, and no one is TOLD to be excluded. text: And that person can identify themselves as one or the other. The film offers us all, an invitation to reflect and examine ourselves. And then when we identify our own lack of commitment to the Saviour of the world; we can get to work. With the supreme importance of what is called the end game. The end game is a term that means winning the game at the end. We must get to work and commit ourselves unconditionally, to be as obedient to God and his commandments and laws as possible. Prior to making such a decision we have to always know with certainty that God loves us that he knows that we are human and that he understands and that he wants us to be happy. We should never be afraid of God because we are sinners and human. We are all going to sin. The effect of sin is alienation from God. All of this alienation, shame guilt etc, will be overcome because of the power of Love. Love is everything. Once you KNOW God simply wants to be your best friend at all times, then you will no longer be afraid. Your confidence will wax strong in his presence. So make a commitment to yourself to love yourself as best you can and to remember that God loves you more than you do and then get to work and commit yourself unconditionally to being the best son to him that you could possibly be. text: So what are you? A Christian or an Atheist or a Christian atheist or Atheist Christian. Or just a frightened little kids who needs to learn to be more open about what you really are, and join the human race. Everyone has difficulties and pain and fear. Do not fear God, whatever you conceive Him to be. And find Him. He loves you. Within the sphere of influence called love, is happiness joy and laughter fun sheer delight and an attitude of goodwill towards all of our brothers and sisters on the planet. Just other humans doing life. Some are good and some are bad. If you are a bad person then none of what I am speaking about will interest you. Because I am talking about becoming a true follower of Jesus Christ. Or, if you don't want to consider yourself a follower of Jesus Christ. Then consider yourself a follower of good. Goodness here is what we're after. And goodness is always beautiful. So, if you like goodness you like it because it is beautiful. Or if you like beauty you like it because it is good. So make a decision to become a good person, a beautiful person. Then watch the cat approach you and purr while rubbing back and forth on your leg. When cats do that, they are giving Love and receiving Love. Both you and the cat gain-another way to describe what I mean is this: Then watch the Stars line up for you. Or another way to describe this is to simply say the universe will take care of you. Part of that care will be your own ability to recognize when they have interceded on your behalf. You must be able to recognize when the universe cares for you, because the universe wants you to know that  they are taking care of you. And the good that comes out of that for you will be that you will witness of it to others. That you will be able to say to other people that the universe takes care of you, that you are loved, that you are liked, that you are important to intelligent  beings. That they are with you to help you win your own race to be won. And you KNOW now, that you can only win your race by helping the human race with their race. Once you know this and speak about this with others ( as I can ), you will win. Your winning your race will not be at the expense of others losing their race. Your winning your race will happen because you helped others. You helped others to win their race. That is what the universe is wanting you to know. And it is the same with mere Christianity. Jesus Christ wants you to know that you will succeed in your personal life as you help others to succeed in their personal life. This is called: The Law of the Harvest. And to a Christian like me Jesus Christ is the Lord of the Harvest. He harvests us!!!!!!! All of creation, except "darkness" wants you to share in their joy-which is to know as they know-that you are IMPORTANT, that you are LOVED üëë

text: For most of the stories, I say sure. ¬†I am all for people letting their beliefs comfort them. ¬†I don't take comfort in something that I can't believe is true, but that is what makes this country great. ¬†However, it is easy to see that Pure Flix is going to keep up their trend of playing on the persecution complex of Christians in the U.S., even when the story isn't structured around one of their hypothetical, "people are out to get us", scenarios. ¬†If you are a government employee, carrying out your duties on the taxpayers' dime, you cannot act in a way that favors any religion while doing so. ¬†We prevent any religious establishment by government or its on-duty employees only because the contrary is less feasible; if we allowed monuments of every religion on public ground, we would be spending heinous sums of money to do so, which makes it easier to just prevent any (even if the monuments were privately funded, the upkeep is left to the government). ¬†Is this hypothetical persecuted Christian EMT going to provide a prayer to Allah, Brahma, and Odin as well? ¬†No, because he should be doing his job and trying to save someone's life instead of proselytizing to them. ¬†You may say, "Oh, we are saving his afterlife!", but a secular government cannot consider that a defense, even if everyone in the country believed that. ¬†In short, the rest of the movie doesn't look that unappealing if you are a believer. ¬†That said, pandering to the fears of Christians who think they are being persecuted because the government is unwilling to cater to beliefs they think should take precedence is really offensive. ¬†Pure Flix shows that they are willing to lie to their audience about how reality works in regards to religious rights in this country.

text: "I save these people. I should get the credit."  Do any believers here relate at all to the sense of incincerity and inauthenticity of such a statement, made by the doctor character?  It's one thing to believe in miricles, but why strawman this point that is made by critics of religion? In essence, what's often said, and I would stand behind, is that doctors and researchers of medicine are denied credit when people see the healing of their loved ones as a miricle. All credit is instead given to an invisible being.   In the real trauma of such situations, it's inappropriate to correct them, just as it should be seen as inappropriate for evangelists to target converting people in such times of weakness.  Do you really believe that an Atheist doctor would say such a thing without a humorous tone? Not a blogger or commenting critic of religion,  but a doctor? Really?  Does it not feel the slightest bit deceitful of the creators of this movie to pretend and imply that a doctor wants to be seen as a god, just because some people think that doctors deserve more credit?   Honestly, I really want to know if you are a believer in an invisible supernatural creator god Yahweh and if you do or don't see this bit of deception going on in that one line..

text: *Just because God is a loving God doesn't mean He will make our lives perfect. If you had a child, would you give it everything it ever wanted? Would you spoil it to the point where there's nothing left to give? Or would you nurture it, let it grow and blossom, discipline them out of the kindness of your heart? ‚ô• God is still love. He gives breath and He takes it away. He determines how long or short our lives are. People are asking me WHY does God allow suffering. Because without pain we would never need God. God wants YOU to feel your need of Him. That's all. Trust, Faith, Hope, Love.. And then peace. If your child never experienced hurt, never failed in life, what would the point of you being the parent be??? They wouldnt need your protection. They wouldn't come to you for help. Now apply this to God, as the Father. We His children may suffer, but let it always be in the glory of His everlasting name!*
